            <thetext>Be able to react on user dragging the page to « before » the beginning (i.e. like many apps implement a &quot;reload ») and « after » the end (i.e. like many apps implement a « fetch next records »).

The pageEnd event on the Scroll container works ok but there are some limitations (that might however be the desired behavior) :

1/ It only triggers if the contained elements actually overflow the visible space.
2/ There is no pageBegin event.

A good approach could be inspired from :

http://imakewebthings.com/jquery-waypoints/</thetext>
